{
  "answer": "In Iqbal's \"Husn o Ishq,\" beauty (*husn*) and love (*ishq*) are presented as dynamically interdependent: beauty acts as the catalyst that perfects and directs love, while love finds its fulfillment and form in response to beauty's manifestation.[^1] Ghalib, by contrast, renders their relation aporetic—beauty persists indifferently or even thrives in love's absence, while love devolves into obsession or wildness (*vehshat*), with no clear resolution or mutual necessity.[^2]\n\n**Iqbal stages unity:**  \n> You are the lightning-flash of Beauty; I, Love's culmination,  \n> If You are dawn, my tears become Your dew's creation.  \n> From Beauty, Love's own nature is spurred toward perfection;  \n> From You, the saplings of my hopes find green direction.[^1]\n\nHere, love completes beauty's flash and supplies its dew, while beauty propels love to maturity—like lightning igniting a storm, or dawn drawing forth responsive tears.\n\n**Ghalib stages rupture:**  \n> Indifferent Beauty is the one to pay for a new display;  \n> The mirror, lost in thought, invents the way for a new display.[^3]\n\nBeauty, self-sufficient and carefree (*beparwa*), purchases its own splendor from the mirror's invention; love is extraneous, a mere observer to beauty's autonomous reinvention. Even when the lover departs, beauty's glance relaxes into cruel repose, unburdened.[^4]\n\nIqbal's interdependence elevates both to cosmic purpose; Ghalib's aporia leaves love yearning amid beauty's careless commerce.\n\n[^1]: Allama Iqbal, *Bang-E-Dara Part 2*, \"Husn o Ishq\" [paragraphs](/works/allama-iqbal-bang-e-dara-part-2-9bc58c/13-husn-o-ishq/translation/#p-73eab8).\n\n[^3]: Mirza Ghalib, *Diwan-E-Ghalib*, \"Husn-e-beparwa kharidar-e-mata-e-jalwa hai\" [paragraph](/works/mirza-ghalib-diwan-e-ghalib-74ed4c/79-husn-e-beparwa-kharidar-e-mata-e-jalwa-hai/translation/#p-6fb822).\n\n[^4]: Mirza Ghalib, *Diwan-E-Ghalib*, \"Husn ghamze ki kashakash se chhoota mere baad\" [paragraph](/works/mirza-ghalib-diwan-e-ghalib-74ed4c/78-husn-ghamze-ki-kashakash-se-chhoota-mere-baad/translation/#p-c31d96).",
